  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT357-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">tōḻi kiḻavaṉ kēṭkum aṇmaiyaṉākak kiḻattikkuc colliyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered to HER, while HE was close [enough] to hear, by
          the confidante. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT357">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> muṉipaṭa ruḻanta pāṭi luṇkaṭ</l>
          <l> paṉikāl pōḻntu paṇaiyeḻiṉ ñekiḻtōṇ</l>
          <l> melliya vākaliṉ mēvarat tiraṇṭu</l>
          <l> nalla veṉṉuñ collai maṉṉiya</l>
          <l> vēṉalañ ciṟutiṉai kākkuñ cēṇōṉ</l>
          <l> ñekiḻiyiṟ peyarnta neṭunal yāṉai</l>
          <l> mīṉpaṭu cuṭaroḷi verūum</l>
          <l> vāṉṟōy veṟpaṉ maṇavā vūṅkē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Such that they came close to the word that says: “good [are] they</l>
          <l>[and] round so that wishes arise, because they [are] soft”,</l>
          <l>[were] the shoulders [now] emaciating,</l>
          <l rend="indent9">having crossed the time of dew ,</l>
          <l>[and the] collyrium eyes without sleeping, enduring hateful affliction</l>
          <l>– before he united with them,</l>
          <l rend="indent6">the man from the sky-touching mountains,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where the tall good elephant, [once] moved by the firebrand</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of the watchman who guards the little Ēṉal millet ,</l>
          <l rend="indent">is frightened at the glowing brightness falling from a star.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
